Introduction (100–150 words)

In today’s digital world, having strong digital literacy skills is essential for students. This project was designed to help us understand how to use digital tools
effectively, communicate professionally, and stay safe online. As a Student Digital Ambassador, the objective was to create a portfolio that demonstrates awareness of
digital platforms, responsible online behavior, and cybersecurity practices.

Through this project, I explored various tools such as GitHub, Google Forms, and coding platforms, and learned how to build a professional digital presence. Each task
focused on a different aspect of digital literacy, including infographic creation, portfolio building, platform usage, email etiquette, and cybercrime awareness. This
project has helped me develop practical skills that will be useful throughout my academic and professional journey.

🟢 Task 1 Write-up (150–200 words)

For Task 1, I created a digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva. The infographic highlights key concepts such as the importance of digital literacy, safe
internet practices, and maintaining a professional online presence. I included visual elements like icons, headings, and short descriptions to make the content easy to
understand and engaging for students.

The design focuses on spreading awareness among my peers about how digital literacy impacts academic success and personal safety. While creating the infographic, I found
it interesting to experiment with layouts and color combinations to make the content visually appealing. One challenge I faced was selecting the most relevant information
and presenting it in a limited space without overcrowding the design.

Overall, this task helped me understand how visual communication can be used effectively to educate others and convey important information in a simple and attractive
format.

🟢 Task 2 Write-up (150–200 words)

In Task 2, I built my student digital portfolio by creating and updating profiles on platforms such as GitHub, LinkedIn, and HackerRank. GitHub was used to host my
project repository and showcase my work, while LinkedIn helped me create a professional profile with my academic details. HackerRank was used to practice coding and
improve my problem-solving skills.

Each platform serves a unique purpose. GitHub acts as a portfolio for projects, LinkedIn helps in networking and career opportunities, and HackerRank enhances coding 
abilities. Over the next four years, I plan to regularly update these platforms by adding new projects, achievements, and skills.

This task helped me understand the importance of maintaining a professional online presence and how these platforms can contribute to internships and job opportunities
in the future.

🟢 Task 3 Write-up (150–200 words)

For Task 3, I explored coding and collaboration platforms. I created an account on HackerRank and completed a beginner-level problem, which helped me understand the

basics of coding and problem-solving. It gave me confidence to start practicing more coding questions in the future.

In addition, I created a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz using Google Forms. The quiz consisted of five questions, including multiple-choice and short-answer types. This activity helped me learn how to create surveys and collect responses efficiently using digital tools.

These platforms are very useful for academic growth. Coding platforms help in developing logical thinking and programming skills, while tools like Google Forms are usefu
l for data collection, surveys, and collaboration. This task gave me practical exposure to tools that I will use frequently during my academic journey.

🟢 Task 4 Write-up (100–150 words)

Task 4 focused on professional communication and email etiquette. I wrote two emails—one requesting an assignment extension and another applying for an internship. This
helped me understand the importance of writing clear subject lines, using a polite tone, and structuring emails properly.

Poor digital communication can lead to misunderstandings and missed opportunities. For example, an unclear or informal email to a professor may not be taken seriously.
Such situations can be avoided by following proper email etiquette, including respectful language and clear communication.

This task improved my ability to communicate professionally and highlighted the importance of maintaining a positive digital image.

🟢 Task 5 Write-up (100–150 words)

While working on Task 5, I researched phishing attacks as a type of cybercrime. I was surprised by how realistic these attacks can be and how easily people can be tricked
into sharing sensitive information. Attackers often create fake websites and messages that look identical to real ones.

This task made me more aware of the importance of verifying links and avoiding suspicious messages. One habit I will change is being more cautious before clicking on any 
unknown links or sharing personal information online. I will also enable two-factor authentication for better security.

Overall, this task increased my awareness of cyber threats and how to prevent them.

🟢 Conclusion (100 words)

This project provided valuable insights into digital literacy and its importance in today’s world. I learned how to use digital tools effectively, build a professional
online presence, and communicate responsibly. The tasks also helped me understand the risks associated with cybercrime and how to stay safe online.

By completing this project, I have developed practical skills that will benefit me in academics and future career opportunities. It has also encouraged me to continuously improve my digital knowledge and use technology in a responsible and productive manner.
